{"lemma":"دَعَةُ","slug":"دَعَةُ","root":"#.د.ع","root_slug":"_-د-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/_-د-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n12559","n44501"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"calmness, comfort, prosperity, welfare"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/da.ʕa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12559","headword_ar":"دَعَّهُ","root":"dE","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Z,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daE~N","text_ar":"دَعٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pushed him, thrust him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drove him, away; he repelled him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did so harshly, roughly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"violently."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, K.) Hence, in the Kur [cvii. 2],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fa*`lika Al~a*iY yaduE~u Alyatiyma","text_ar":"فَذٰلِكَ الَّذِى يَدُعُّ اليَتِيمَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That is he who pusheth, thrusteth,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"driveth, away the orphan:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who doth so harshly, roughly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"violently:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who treateth the orphan with harshness, roughness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"violence; pushing, thrusting,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"driving, away; and chiding with rudeness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coarseness."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Z, TA.) And in like manner, in the same [lii. 13],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yawoma yudaE~uwna A_ilaY naAri","text_ar":"يَوْمَ يُدَعُّونَ اـِلَى نَارِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jahan~ama daE~FA","text_ar":"جَهَنَّمَ دَعًّا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"On the day when they shall be pushed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thrust,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"driven, with harshness, roughness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"violence, to the fire of Hell."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A 'Obeyd, Bd, Jel, TA.) And in a trad. of Esh-Shaabee,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAnuwA","text_ar":"كَانُوا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laA yudaE~uwna Eanohu","text_ar":"لَا يُدَعُّونَ عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They used not to be driven, nor pushed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repelled, from it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Z","K","Bd","Jel"]},{"entry_id":"n44501","headword_ar":"دَعَةٌ","root":"wdE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ease; repose; freedom from trouble or inconvenience, and toil or fatigue; tranquillity;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xafoDN","text_ar":"خَفْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S. Mgh, K, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raAHapN","text_ar":"رَاحَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukuwnN","text_ar":"سُكُونٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ampleness of circumstances"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEapN","text_ar":"سَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") in life: (K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daEapN","text_ar":"دَعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is syn. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rAHp","text_ar":"راحة"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"skwn","text_ar":"سكون"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xafoDN","text_ar":"خَفْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies “ ampleness of the circumstances ” ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEah~N","text_ar":"سَعَهٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":") of life, and “ plentifulness and pleasantness ” thereof: [see an ex. of both, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xafoDN","text_ar":"خَفْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (El-Marzookee and MF, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xfD","text_ar":"خفض"},{"kind":"text","text":".)       -A2-  See 1 and 3."}],"source_refs":["Mgh","Msb","TA","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}